## 10. Do's and Don'ts

### ✅ DO

- Keep the UI full-screen and presentation-ready (no browser chrome clutter)
- Use the dark theme consistently
- Make logos square with rounded corners
- Show all 7 columns even if some are empty
- Keep the cover page simple and clean
- Use deterministic mocking (same company → same category/type every time)
- Handle image loading errors gracefully
- Use semantic HTML and accessible markup

### ❌ DON'T

- Don't show company names on the board — logos only
- Don't show deal stages that are not in the 7 specified stages
- Don't add scrolling to the presentation board — everything must fit
- Don't use light theme or white backgrounds
- Don't hardcode deal data — always parse from CSV
- Don't require a backend or database for the MVP
- Don't use CSS modules or styled-components — use Tailwind
- Don't add mobile responsiveness — this is desktop-only